`SpatialData` visualization

Source: R/plot.R
plotSpatialData.Rd

...

Usage

plotSpatialData()

# S4 method for class 'SpatialData'
plotImage(x, i = 1, j = 1, k = NULL)

# S4 method for class 'SpatialData'
plotLabel(x, i = 1, c = NULL, a = 0.5, pal = hcl.colors(11, "Spectral"))

# S4 method for class 'SpatialData'
plotPoint(x, i = 1, c = NULL, s = 1, a = 1)

# S4 method for class 'PointFrame'
plotPoint(x, c = NULL, s = 1, a = 1)

# S4 method for class 'SpatialData'
plotShape(x, i = 1, c = NULL, f = "white", s = "radius", a = 0.2)

Arguments

x

SpatialData

i

Index of which slot of the Shape layer. Default value is 1.

j

name of target coordinate system.

k

index of the scale of an image (default: NULL)

c, f, s, a

plotting aesthetics; color, fill, size, alpha.

a

Transparency of the shape to plot. A value ranges from 0 to 1, with decreasing visibility. Default value is 0.2.

pal

character vector of colors; will interpolate automatically when insufficient values are provided.

s

Size of the shape to plot. Default is "radius".

c

Color border of the shape to plot. Default value is NULL.

Value

ggplot
